  "texts": [
    "Datasets used in this study lack POS information making it crucial to correctly label nested NEs.",
    "The challenge of nested NEs is addressed by employing word embeddings in the proposed approach.",
    "Both Floret and FastText embeddings utilize sub-word information, by breaking each word into possible sub-words that help to capture morphological leads to create contextual relationships among words.",
    "This is essential to correctly label nested NEs, as the meaning of a sub-word commonly depends on the larger word associated with it.",
    "For instance, in the sentence \" ‫ﺷ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ﮦ‬ ‫ﺟ‬ ‫ﮩ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ں‬ ‫ﻧ‬ ‫ﮯ‬ ‫ﺗ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ج‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﺤ‬ ‫ﻞ‬ ‫آ‬ ‫ﮔ‬ ‫ﺮ‬ ‫ﮦ‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﯿ‬ ‫ﮟ‬ ‫ﺑ‬ ‫ﻨ‬ ‫ﻮ‬ ‫ا‬ ‫ﯾ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ، ‫ﺟ‬ ‫ﻮ‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﻐ‬ ‫ﻞ‬ ‫ﺑ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫د‬ ‫ﺷ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ﮨ‬ ‫ﻮ‬ ‫ں‬ ‫ﮐ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﻘ‬ ‫ﺒ‬ ‫ﺮ‬ ‫ﮦ‬ ‫ﮨ‬ ‫ﮯ‬ \" -/Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal in Agra, which is the tomb of the Mughal emperors, \" ‫ﺗ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ج‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﺤ‬ ‫ﻞ‬ ‫آ‬ ‫ﮔ‬ ‫ﺮ‬ ‫ﮦ‬ \" -/Taj Mahal Agra is a nested entity within \" ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﻐ‬ ‫ﻞ‬ ‫ﺑ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫د‬ ‫ﺷ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ﮨ‬ ‫ﻮ‬ ‫ں‬ ‫ﮐ‬ ‫ﺎ‬ ‫ﻣ‬ ‫ﻘ‬ ‫ﺒ‬ ‫ﺮ‬ ‫ﮦ‬ \" -/tomb of the Mughal emperors."
